    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sheets of lightweight paper, bearing an official postal stamp imprint, that are folded to form their own envelopes and can be sent via airmail at a special, low rate.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046682/Random House Dictionary of the English Language (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hojas de papel liviano, que portan una impresión postal oficial de sello, que se dobla para formar su propio sobre y se puede enviar por correo aéreo con una tasa especial rebajada.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lichte vellen papier met een officieel poststempel, die worden opgevouwen om zo hun eigen enveloppe te vormen en die tegen een speciaal, laag tarief via luchtpost kunnen worden verstuurd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
